race.comment: FLAMIN' JOE (2) was in hot form, winning three on end before being checked in the run last time and finishing eighth in a Grade 5 at Bulli (23.30). Has good speed and aided by a low draw. Has the ability and looks a key chance. SILVERTREE SCAR (8) failed to come into contention last start after being shuffled back early at this track, but prior to that won by 1.75 lengths at Wagga (18.50) beating House Money in a Maiden on October 3. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. Can figure in the finish. AL CAN DO (3) steps out for the first time at this course. In the money last start when second (17.70) at Taree Super Track over 300m. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Will give a great sight again. CHEERS BILLY (4) will run well despite no experience on this track.

runners.name: Cheers Billy
